---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Income Smoothing Calculator",
  "description": "Plan your retirement withdrawals to minimize lifetime taxes by keeping your taxable income consistent year over year.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "FireMaths"
  },
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is income smoothing in retirement?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Income smoothing is the strategy of withdrawing from a mix of taxable, tax-deferred, and tax-free accounts to maintain a consistent taxable income level, thereby preventing your income from spiking into higher marginal tax brackets."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why does income smoothing save taxes?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Because the US tax system is progressive, a $100,000 withdrawal in one year and $0 the next is taxed at a much higher total rate than two $50,000 withdrawals spread across both years."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does this relate to RMDs?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "By intentionally taking withdrawals or converting traditional IRA funds to Roth (smoothing your income up to the top of a low tax bracket) in early retirement, you reduce the size of your pre-tax accounts. This lowers your eventual Required Minimum Distributions (RMDs), preventing a massive tax bomb later in life."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
};

export const meta = {
  title: "Income Smoothing Calculator",
  description: "Plan your retirement withdrawals to minimize lifetime taxes by keeping taxable income consistent across years. Model Roth conversions and bracket optimization.",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="firemaths"
  title="Income Smoothing Calculator"
  description="Plan your withdrawals to minimize lifetime taxes by keeping your taxable income consistent."
  canonical="https://firemaths.info/income-smoothing-calculator"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Income Smoothing Calculator</h1>
      <p>A flatter tax curve means hundreds of thousands of dollars saved.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>Smooth Your Withdrawals</h2>
      <p>Model the optimal mix of account withdrawals to hit your spending goal without spiking your marginal tax bracket.</p>

      <div class="calculator-form">
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="annualSpending">Annual Spending Goal</label>
          <div class="input-prefix">
            <span>$</span>
            <input type="number" id="annualSpending" value="80000" min="0" step="1000" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="taxBracketTarget">Target Taxable Income Bracket (Single Filer - 2024)</label>
          <select id="taxBracketTarget">
            <option value="14600">0% (Standard Deduction - $14,600)</option>
            <option value="26200">10% Bracket (Up to $26,200)</option>
            <option value="61750" selected>12% Bracket (Up to $61,750)</option>
            <option value="115125">22% Bracket (Up to $115,125)</option>
          </select>
        </div>

        <button id="calcBtn" class="calc-btn">Calculate Withdrawal Mix</button>
      </div>

      <div class="results" id="results" style="display:none;">
        <h3 style="margin-top:0">Optimal Withdrawal Plan:</h3>

        <div class="results-grid" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #f39c12;">
            <p style="margin:0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-secondary)">From Traditional (Pre-Tax) Accounts</p>
            <h3 id="resPreTax" style="margin:0; font-size: 1.5rem; color: #f39c12">$0</h3>
            <p style="margin:0; font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-secondary)">This fills up your target bracket and standard deduction.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #3498db;">
            <p style="margin:0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-secondary)">From Roth (Post-Tax) Accounts</p>
            <h3 id="resRoth" style="margin:0; font-size: 1.5rem; color: #3498db">$0</h3>
            <p style="margin:0; font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-secondary)">This covers the rest of your spending goal entirely tax-free.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">By mixing these withdrawals, you hit your <strong>$80,000</strong> spending goal but your taxable income is only high enough to reach the top of your selected bracket. This "smooths" your taxes over time compared to draining pre-tax accounts all at once.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card content-section">
      <h2>The Mechanics of Income Smoothing</h2>
      <p>As discussed in our <a href="/tax-optimization-fire-guide">Tax Optimization FIRE Guide</a>, progressive tax brackets punish uneven income. Earning $200k in one year and $0 the next results in a drastically higher lifetime tax bill than earning $100k for two years.</p>

      <h3>Required Minimum Distributions (RMDs)</h3>
      <p>The government requires you to start withdrawing from pre-tax accounts at age 73. If you have a massive Traditional IRA, these RMDs can force you into the 32% or 35% tax brackets during your 80s.</p>
      <p>To prevent this, early retirees practice income smoothing by intentionally taking pre-tax distributions (or Roth Conversions) in their 40s and 50s. By voluntarily paying 10% or 12% tax now, they shrink the pre-tax account balance, thereby defusing the future RMD tax bomb.</p>

      <h3>The ACA Subsidy Cliff</h3>
      <p>For early retirees, your taxable income also dictates your Affordable Care Act (ACA) health insurance premiums. If your income spikes, you could lose thousands of dollars in subsidies. A smoothed income keeps your MAGI consistent, allowing you to reliably predict and optimize your healthcare costs.</p>

      <h3>How to Implement This Strategy</h3>
      <p>Our <a href="/guide-tax-efficient-withdrawal">Guide to Tax Efficient Withdrawals</a> goes deeper into the exact order of operations. In general, you want to withdraw from your Traditional IRA until you hit the top of your target tax bracket, and then cover the remaining lifestyle expenses with tax-free Roth or HSA funds.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.getElementById('calcBtn').addEventListener('click', function() {
      const spending = parseFloat(document.getElementById('annualSpending').value) || 0;
      const targetBracket = parseFloat(document.getElementById('taxBracketTarget').value) || 0;

      let preTaxWithdrawal = Math.min(spending, targetBracket);
      let rothWithdrawal = spending - preTaxWithdrawal;

      if (rothWithdrawal < 0) rothWithdrawal = 0;

      document.getElementById('resPreTax').innerText = '$' + preTaxWithdrawal.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 0, maximumFractionDigits: 0});
      document.getElementById('resRoth').innerText = '$' + rothWithdrawal.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 0, maximumFractionDigits: 0});

      document.getElementById('results').querySelector('p').innerHTML = `By mixing these withdrawals, you hit your <strong>$${spending.toLocaleString()}</strong> spending goal but your taxable income is only high enough to reach the top of your selected bracket. This "smooths" your taxes over time compared to draining pre-tax accounts all at once.`;

      document.getElementById('results').style.display = 'block';
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    }
    .hero {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
    }
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .hero p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .card {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
    }
    .calculator-form {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .input-group {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .input-prefix {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 6px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .input-prefix span {
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .input-prefix input, select {
      flex: 1;
      padding: 0.5rem;
      border: none;
      background: transparent;
      color: inherit;
      font-size: 1rem;
      outline: none;
    }
    select {
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 6px;
      background: #111;
      padding: 0.6rem;
    }
    .calc-btn {
      background: var(--accent-color);
      color: #000;
      border: none;
      padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-weight: bold;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-size: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
      transition: opacity 0.2s;
    }
    .calc-btn:hover {
      opacity: 0.9;
    }
    .results {
      padding-top: 1.5rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    }
    .content-section h2, .content-section h3 {
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }
    .content-section p, .content-section li {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    a {
      color: var(--accent-color);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="related-tools" style="margin-top:3rem;padding-top:2rem;border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);">
    <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">🔗 Related Tools</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(280px,1fr));gap:1rem;">
      <a href="/guide-tax-efficient-withdrawal" style="display:block;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:10px;padding:1.25rem;text-decoration:none;color:inherit;transition:border-color 0.2s,transform 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='rgba(255,255,255,0.2)';this.style.transform='translateY(-2px)'" onmouseout="this.style.borderColor='rgba(255,255,255,0.08)';this.style.transform='none'">
        <strong style="font-size:0.95rem;">Guide to Tax-Efficient Withdrawals</strong>
        <p style="opacity:0.6;font-size:0.83rem;margin:0.4rem 0 0;line-height:1.4;">Learn the optimal order to withdraw from retirement accounts. Covers Roth conversions, tax bracket management, and accou...</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>
